            <div>
              <strong>Find Your Stopcock</strong>
              <p>In most Liverpool properties it is under the kitchen sink, in a hallway cupboard or under the stairs. Victorian terraces often have it in the cellar or near the front door. Turn it clockwise to stop all water.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="selfhelp-step">
            <div class="selfhelp-num">2</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Check Your Boiler Pressure</strong>
              <p>If your boiler shows a fault code or you have no hot water, check the pressure gauge. It should read between 1 and 1.5 bar. Below 0.5 bar you can repressurise using the filling loop.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="selfhelp-step">
            <div class="selfhelp-num">3</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Check Your Neighbours</strong>
              <p>If you have no water or heating, check whether your neighbours are affected. If they are, it is a <a href="https://www.unitedutilities.com/help-and-support/emergencies/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--navy);font-weight:700;">United Utilities</a> network fault. Call 0345 672 3723. For general water supply guidance visit <a href="https://www.water.org.uk/consumers/stopcock" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--navy);font-weight:700;">Water UK</a>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="selfhelp-warning">
          <span style="font-size:1.2rem;">⚠</span>
          <p>If you smell gas at any point, stop immediately and call <a href="https://cadentgas.com/gas-escapes" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--red);font-weight:700;">Cadent Gas Emergency on 0800 111 999</a>. Do not attempt any checks yourself. For general gas safety advice visit <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/domestic/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--red);font-weight:700;">HSE gas safety guidance</a>.</p>
